{"key":"processedPost-10270457","value":{"id":10270457,"first":10270033,"last":10271065,"when":1241230200,"utime":"05/02/09 05:10 AM","content":"The overpressure plug on a canner does not seal below 0 PSI, thus they don't hold a vacuum.&nbsp; You'd need to replace the nozzle and weight with a toggle valve, and replace the blowout plug with one made for a sterilizer.&nbsp; However, that only leaves you with one means of overpressure protection.&nbsp; Sterilizers have two: A blowout plug and a spring actuated relief valve, thus they're safer.<br />RR","title":"Re: A Little confusion- converting an All American 921 into a sterilizer"}}